---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const email = "shiri@yourfamilypaediatrician.com";
const lastUpdated = "4 July 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy — Your Family Paediatrician"
  description="How Your Family Paediatrician handles the personal information you share through this website."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <article class="policy">
        <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
        <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

        <p>
          This website belongs to Dr Shiri Lejay, Consultant Paediatrician,
          trading as Your Family Paediatrician ("I", "me"). I am the data
          controller for the personal information collected through this
          website. You can contact me about anything in this policy at
          <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>What I collect</h2>
        <p>
          The only personal information this website collects is what you
          choose to send me through the booking form (or by emailing me
          directly): your name, email address, phone number (optional), your
          child's age, the topic you'd like help with, and your message.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your message may include information about your child's health.
          Health information is special-category data under UK data protection
          law — please share only what you feel is needed for me to help; we
          can discuss the details when I reply.
        </p>
        <p>
          This website sets no cookies and uses no analytics or tracking of
          any kind.
        </p>

        <h2>How I use it</h2>
        <p>
          I use the information you send solely to respond to your enquiry and
          to arrange your appointment. The legal bases for this are taking
          steps at your request before entering into a contract, and — for any
          health information you choose to include — your consent, which you
          can withdraw at any time by contacting me.
        </p>
        <p>I never sell or share your information for marketing.</p>

        <h2>Where it goes and how long it's kept</h2>
        <p>
          This website is hosted by Netlify, which processes form submissions
          on my behalf and may do so on servers outside the UK, subject to the
          safeguards in its data processing agreement. Form submissions are
          automatically deleted from Netlify within 7 days; your enquiry is
          delivered to my practice email inbox, where I keep it only as long
          as needed to handle your enquiry and meet my professional
          record-keeping obligations.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you go on to have a consultation, your clinical records are held
          by Central Health London under its own privacy policy.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to ask for a copy of the information I hold about
          you, to have it corrected or deleted, to restrict or object to its
          use, to receive it in a portable format, and to withdraw consent.
          To exercise any of these, email
          <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>. You can also complain to
          the Information Commissioner's Office at
          <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
            >ico.org.uk</a
          >.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          Any changes to this policy will be posted on this page with an
          updated date above.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy {
    max-width: 42em;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.625rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .updated {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: #8a9893;
  }

  h2 {
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 15.5px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent-deep);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  a:hover,
  a:focus-visible {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
  }
</style>
